            "answer_text": "Hi. First of all I apology if I make mistakes writing in English. My native language is Spanish. The expresi\u00f3n you\u2019re asking about is translated into Spanish in two ways: Gracias, mi amor.Gracias, amor m\u00edo.But you could also use other nice expressions to communicate your thanks with love. For example: Gracias, dulzura.Gracias, cari\u00f1o.Gracias, cielo.Gracias, mi cielo.Gracias, adorado m\u00edo/adorada m\u00eda.Gracias, lindura.Gracias, hermosa [It is no common to hear someone say the phrase \u201cGracias, hermoso\u201d to a man, but you could use it if you want and no problem!].Gracias, preciosaGracias, guapo/guapa.Gracias, tesoro.And finally here is my favorite expression that I say to my partner: Gracias, sexy!I don't remember any more nice expressions but if anyone else has any other, please share it with us! ",
